        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add secure bridge artifact transfer",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- transfer ChatGPT-generated files from a browser bridge host back to the client through a token-protected pull endpoint\n- advertise protocol support and size limits through `/health` capability negotiation\n- sanitize filenames and verify byte count, SHA-256, and ZIP structure before publishing client-local artifacts\n- preserve text responses and provide a manual-copy fallback for mixed-version or failed transfers\n- expose validation and transfer metadata in stored sessions and bridge diagnostics\n\n## Security\n\nThe NDJSON result contains only redacted descriptors. It does not expose host filesystem paths, ChatGPT cookies, bridge credentials, or signed download URLs. Artifact fetches reuse the existing bridge bearer token and expire from the host registry after a bounded TTL.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm run format:check`\n- `pnpm run lint`\n- `pnpm run build`\n- targeted bridge/browser tests: 43 passed\n- full unit suite: 1,340 passed, 43 skipped\n- live Windows browser host -> cloud Linux client smoke: generated ZIP transferred to the Linux session artifact directory with matching SHA-256, valid ZIP structure, and `transfer=completed`\n",
